                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid amaranth)</seg>
                        Scribe: Ḫāyla Māryām. Additio 1
                        mentions ʾabuna Ḫāyla Māryām as the scribe. His name has been also added
                        into the concluding supplication formula on <locus target="#52ra">52ra</locus>, in the main hand, in strong vermilion.<date>Second half of
                           the 20th cent.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist; two groups of
                           lines and one line on the incipit page; one or two initial lines of the
                           sections; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2va">f. 2va</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.  </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#2va">2va</locus>: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘአባ፡ ኃይለ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘወሀቦ፡
                              ለዮሐንስ፡ ዘደብረ፡ ናዝሬት፡ ወዘአጽሐፎ፡ ጌታየ፡ ሸቴ፡ ወጸሐፊሁ፡ ኃጥእ፡ አቡነ፡ ኃይለ፡
                              ማርም[sic]</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> The note is written in the main hand. It states
                           that the Ms. belongs to ʾabbā Ḫāyla Mikāʾel who donated it to the church
                           of Yoḥannǝs of Dabra Nazret. The book was commissioned by Getayä Šäte and
                           was written by ʾabuna<note> Ḫāyla Māryām. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Omitted letters or words are inserted interlineally, in
                           ink or in pen: <locus target="#4rb">4rb</locus>, 5rb, 7vb, 16rb, 19rb,
                           21ra, 22ra, 25va, 33ra, 36va, 39vb, 47v, 51rb. 
 - Illegible note in
                           pencil: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days written in the upper margin, in a secondary hand, in pen: ሰኑይ:
                                 <locus target="#3ra">fol. 3ra</locus> ረውዕ[sic], ዘረብዕ: <locus target="#24r">fol. 24r</locus> ሐሙስ: <locus target="#34ra">fol.
                                 34ra</locus> አርብ: <locus target="#38vb">fol. 38vb</locus> ቀዳም:
                                 <locus target="#43vb">fol. 43vb</locus> ሰንበት፡ ክር: <locus target="#48r">fol. 48r</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
